It turns out it's relatively simple, but there is one wrinkle.

The solution is simply a #!/usr/bin/env python2.7

The wrinkle is that on many of the machines I use python2.7 is required, just python won't work. So that's what it's set too. Nitpick does require python 2.7 or later in any case.